    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA290-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">1. itu parattai viṟali mēlvaittut talaimakaṉai neruṅkic colliyatu. 2. parattaiyiṉ piriya vāyilāyp pukka pāṇaṉukkut (EN, ER, ET, EV: pāṇaṉ kēṭpa) tōḻi colliyatūumām.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">1. This is what the other women said in the direction of HIM, putting it on the dancing girl. 2. It is also what the confidante said to the brad who had entered as a mediator when [HE] had separated for another woman.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA290">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            vayalveḷ ḷāmpaṟ cūṭutaru putuppūk</l>
<l>            kaṉṟuṭaip puṉiṟṟā tiṉṟa micci</l>
<l>            lōyvuṭai naṭaippaka ṭāru mūraṉ</l>
<l>            ṟoṭarpunī veḵkiṉai yāyi ṉeṉcoṟ</l>
<l>            koḷḷaṉ mātō muḷḷeyiṟ ṟōyē </l>
<l>            nīyē perunalat takaiyē yavaṉē</l>
<l>            neṭunīrp poykai naṭunā ḷeytit</l>
<l>            taṇkamaḻ putumala rūtum</l>
<l>            vaṇṭeṉa moḻipa makaṉeṉ ṉārē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>In case you desired<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">veḵkiṉai āyiṉ</term>: here we have the perfective aspect in order to express the hypothetical conditional.</note> an attachment to the man from the village,</l>
<l rend="indent">where a bull with weary gait feeds on the rest of what was eaten by a cow,</l>
<l rend="indent2">with [her] calf just born, from the new flowers,</l>
<l rend="indent2">given to be worn(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">cūṭu taru</term>: here for once we do not seem to see the auxiliary construction, but its semantic cognate.</note>, of the white waterlilies in the paddy field,</l>
<l>don’t you take my word [for it]<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">koḷḷaṉ mātō</term>: this is a rhetorical problem. How are we to understand <term xml:lang="ta">mātō</term>, an emphatic mark of rhetorical questions expressing astonishment, in connection with an imperative?</note>, you with thorn teeth.</l>
<l>You, [you are] suitable with great beauty.</l>
<l rend="indent3">He,</l>
<l>those who don’t call him ‘son* say *[he is] a bee,</l>
<l rend="indent2">filling himself on cool fragrant new blossoms</l>
<l rend="indent3">when reaching the pond of long water at midday.*</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
